20:32.781 --> 20:35.326
and then mom called and
talked for over an hour.

20:35.367 --> 20:36.785
And you wanted steak instead

20:36.828 --> 20:38.328
of the chicken I'd
already prepared.

20:38.370 --> 20:40.873
Dinner should be on
the table at seven.

20:40.915 --> 20:44.210
I don't expect your mother
to care about such things

20:44.251 --> 20:46.838
since her idea of dinner
was a bucket of chicken

20:46.879 --> 20:48.714
on the table and
nine every night.

20:49.883 --> 20:52.218
But you know how our
household is run.

20:52.260 --> 20:53.677
It'll be ready shortly.

20:54.887 --> 20:58.640
A wife's priority
after God is her husband

20:58.683 --> 21:01.853
and then comes work,
and friends, and family

21:01.895 --> 21:03.312
and that includes your mother

21:04.938 --> 21:06.398
I said, it'll
be ready shortly.

21:06.441 --> 21:08.735
Don't rush past the seasoning.

21:26.168 --> 21:27.377
Yes?

21:27.419 --> 21:30.297
Any other man
would feel unloved

21:30.339 --> 21:33.760
by his wife who was coming
home and not acknowledging him.

21:33.800 --> 21:35.386
I'm just trying to get
your dinner on the table.

21:35.427 --> 21:38.723
Maybe if you cut the
cackle session short

21:38.764 --> 21:39.932
with your mother then

21:39.973 --> 21:41.934
I wouldn't have to
forfeit my greeting.

21:42.894 --> 21:43.895
Good evening Michael.

21:49.983 --> 21:51.026
Wow.

21:52.153 --> 21:53.238
Just like old friends.

22:03.956 --> 22:06.833
Why do you keep testing me?

22:06.876 --> 22:07.751
Testing you?

22:08.919 --> 22:09.753
Nevermind.

22:09.796 --> 22:12.465
No, no, no, no,
explain what you mean.

22:12.507 --> 22:13.341
Nevermind.

22:13.383 --> 22:14.342
I don't want to argue.

22:14.384 --> 22:15.385
So you're okay?

22:15.425 --> 22:16.552
Great.

22:18.972 --> 22:20.223
May I get back to your steak?

22:20.264 --> 22:22.057
I'll be in the dining room.

22:22.099 --> 22:24.101
Oh, and it's almost seven.

22:25.310 --> 22:27.355
You look so much
younger when you smile.

22:28.188 --> 22:29.147
It's nice.

22:35.530 --> 22:37.197
Your mother is
a terrible person.

22:37.240 --> 22:39.325
You only had chicken at nine,

22:39.367 --> 22:41.578
well what's wrong
with freaking chicken?

22:41.618 --> 22:42.453
God.

22:49.251 --> 22:50.211
It's okay.

22:57.676 --> 22:58.511
7:04.

23:42.055 --> 23:43.681
Let's bless this meal no matter

23:43.723 --> 23:45.474
how late it was
put on the table.

23:48.353 --> 23:49.145
Dear Lord.

23:49.186 --> 23:50.396
Thank you for this day

23:50.437 --> 23:52.439
and for this food
that was prepared

23:52.482 --> 23:54.483
for the nourishment
of our bodies

23:54.526 --> 23:58.196
and thank you for the beautiful
hands that prepared it.

24:07.371 --> 24:08.664
I know
it's a little over done.

24:08.705 --> 24:10.290
Nope, come here honey.

24:11.251 --> 24:12.417
Come here.

24:22.177 --> 24:23.470
Look at this here.

24:26.432 --> 24:28.393
How do I like my steak prepared?

24:30.854 --> 24:31.980
I was trying.

24:32.021 --> 24:36.358
Instead of cutting short
the enthralling conversation

24:36.401 --> 24:37.735
you were having
with your mother,

24:37.777 --> 24:42.407
this less than mediocre
meal is my fault?

24:43.491 --> 24:45.285
No, that's not
what I'm saying.

24:49.246 --> 24:50.080
Clean it up.

24:58.505 --> 24:59.381
I'm going out.

25:19.402 --> 25:20.528
Hey babe.

25:20.569 --> 25:23.489
Must be nice to just sit
around all day, watching TV.

25:24.490 --> 25:25.366
Huh?

25:25.407 --> 25:26.783
I've been working all day.

25:30.245 --> 25:31.455
You call what you do work?

25:37.419 --> 25:38.712
You're drinking.

25:41.590 --> 25:42.425
So.

25:43.842 --> 25:46.970
Come sit down, tell
me what's going on.

25:47.012 --> 25:48.388
You fix dinner?

25:48.431 --> 25:50.850
Yes, come sit down.

25:50.892 --> 25:52.352
It's should still be warm.

25:55.896 --> 25:58.691
So what's going on?

26:01.027 --> 26:01.861
Rough night out?

26:08.826 --> 26:11.621
Babe, can you not hear me?

26:11.663 --> 26:13.373
Yeah I hear you.

26:16.542 --> 26:17.918
Dinner is served.

26:21.505 --> 26:22.506
Okay.

26:39.398 --> 26:41.984
So all this shit is funny
right now to you, huh?

26:42.026 --> 26:42.986
What?

26:45.029 --> 26:47.949
I just came home from a
terrible ass day at work,

26:47.991 --> 26:50.033
and you sitting up in
here laughing in my face.

26:50.076 --> 26:52.828
I tried talking to you,
but you didn't respond.

26:53.996 --> 26:55.038
I thought I would
be a bigger help

26:55.080 --> 26:56.582
by just leaving you alone.

26:57.666 --> 27:01.838
Eating popcorn and laughing
in my damn face is helping me?

27:01.879 --> 27:03.130
Am I entertaining you?

27:03.172 --> 27:05.133
I was laughing at
the movie, not you.

27:05.175 --> 27:06.759
You know I wouldn't do that.

27:06.800 --> 27:08.011
What is wrong with you?

27:08.051 --> 27:10.597
Oh, so now I'm the
problem here too?

27:15.184 --> 27:18.396
I don't know what
happened at work,

27:19.771 --> 27:23.400
but we said that we would
stay calm and talk it out.

27:24.610 --> 27:25.819
And are you a
fucking councilor?

27:33.994 --> 27:35.162
Derek.

27:38.165 --> 27:40.835
Derek, calm down.

27:40.876 --> 27:42.837
Don't tell me to calm down.

27:42.878 --> 27:45.005
Derek, Derek.

27:46.257 --> 27:47.759
Get me another beer.

28:09.989 --> 28:13.617
I said, get me another beer.

28:15.869 --> 28:16.870
This one's empty.

28:19.081 --> 28:19.998
Get up.

28:20.040 --> 28:20.958
No, no!

28:21.000 --> 28:22.626
Get up.

28:23.794 --> 28:25.879
No, Derek, please!

28:33.262 --> 28:35.682
And so at this time,

28:35.723 --> 28:38.059
those of you who are
in need of prayer.

28:39.601 --> 28:41.271
Or if you have family

28:41.311 --> 28:45.732
or loved ones in need of
prayer, meet me at the altar.

28:45.774 --> 28:48.235
♪ I surrender ♪

28:50.905 --> 28:51.739
Yes ma'am.

28:51.780 --> 28:54.242
♪ All to him ♪

28:56.953 --> 28:59.079
And God
said, cometh on to me.

29:03.792 --> 29:04.626
Yes sir.

29:08.673 --> 29:10.215
Do I have another?

29:10.258 --> 29:13.011
♪ Love and trust ♪

29:14.887 --> 29:17.182
Come,
leave all your woes

29:17.223 --> 29:19.184
and wills at the alter.

29:19.224 --> 29:24.230
♪ His presence daily leave ♪

29:28.108 --> 29:30.944
♪ I surrender all ♪

29:35.782 --> 29:38.077
Thank you brother.

29:52.966 --> 29:53.967
Excuse me.

29:55.261 --> 29:57.012
I haven't seen you in awhile.

30:00.390 --> 30:02.309
He's not going to change.

30:03.310 --> 30:04.145
You have to.

30:05.104 --> 30:06.981
I have to change?

30:07.022 --> 30:07.982
What?

30:08.023 --> 30:10.025
Be a better wife?

30:10.068 --> 30:11.360
Keep my mouth shut?

30:11.402 --> 30:13.029
Tell me, what do
I need to change?

30:13.070 --> 30:16.741
You have to get out of
there before he kills you.

30:16.782 --> 30:19.202
Like I told you before,
I'm not leaving him.

30:19.243 --> 30:21.328
Derek is a good man deep down.

30:21.370 --> 30:23.665
He pays all the bills, and
he keeps food on the table.

30:23.705 --> 30:24.873
And I'm sure he makes you feel

30:24.915 --> 30:28.086
like the most special
person in the world.

30:28.126 --> 30:29.462
Most of the time.

30:29.503 --> 30:32.965
He needs me, and
Faith and I need him.

30:33.007 --> 30:35.093
He won't stop.

30:35.134 --> 30:37.095
Do you have any idea how hard

30:37.136 --> 30:39.806
it is right now to
be a police officer?

30:39.848 --> 30:43.059
Half of the world hates you
because of the corrupt ones.

30:43.100 --> 30:45.270
Ad being black and
people hate you

30:45.310 --> 30:46.436
because you're a sellout.

30:46.479 --> 30:47.981
Every day he goes out there

30:48.021 --> 30:49.439
and put his life on the line.

30:49.482 --> 30:51.984
And then he comes home
and does this to you.

30:53.569 --> 30:55.405
It isn't okay.

30:55.445 --> 31:00.409
No matter how many lives
he saves, this is not okay.

31:04.998 --> 31:08.501
Is your marriage so perfect
that you can't understand

31:08.542 --> 31:11.044
that couples go through
a few rough patches?

31:11.087 --> 31:13.047
I see how pastor
Jeffrey treats you

31:13.088 --> 31:16.091
but would you leave him if
he was abusive a few times?

31:19.345 --> 31:20.180
Yes.

31:21.973 --> 31:23.015
I would.

31:23.057 --> 31:25.434
Than you're lying to yourself.

31:25.475 --> 31:27.270
It's easy when it's
not your reality

31:29.021 --> 31:31.148
You know they granted
my permit right?

31:31.191 --> 31:34.152
At first we get the program,
then we get the school.

31:34.194 --> 31:36.361
I heard, you know
your little brother,

31:36.404 --> 31:38.198
he already has his own Academy

31:38.239 --> 31:40.575
and a yearly mission
out of his church.

31:44.244 --> 31:45.579
He'll get there.

31:45.621 --> 31:47.581
Oh, that's so nice.

31:48.499 --> 31:51.085
Having your little lady
speak on your behalf.

31:51.126 --> 31:55.964
Be careful, some might consider
that a sign of weakness.

31:56.007 --> 31:57.342
She doesn't speak for me.

31:59.260 --> 32:00.677
And I'll have that
school within a year.

32:00.720 --> 32:02.972
I got the permit, I
will get that school.

32:05.224 --> 32:09.061
Son, you think you got that
permit on your own don't you?

32:12.272 --> 32:13.440
It was you?

32:13.482 --> 32:14.442
I don't mind
throwing my weight

32:14.483 --> 32:16.026
around a little bit for my boy.

32:20.322 --> 32:22.658
Matthew, why don't you go
ahead and get these dishes?

32:22.700 --> 32:24.369
Oh wait, wait a second.

32:24.409 --> 32:26.537
You're having your
boy do dishes?

32:26.578 --> 32:27.496
What are you trying to do,

32:27.539 --> 32:29.249
turn him into a housewife?

32:29.290 --> 32:31.751
Everyone does their part
around here. Mr. Jeffries.

32:31.792 --> 32:32.876
Why don't you come
with your granddad

32:32.918 --> 32:35.713
and we're going to go watch
a game in the living room.

32:35.754 --> 32:38.215
We'll let your mother
and your grandmother,

32:38.258 --> 32:39.759
they'll take care of the dishes.

32:39.800 --> 32:41.593
And I am going to teach you all

32:41.636 --> 32:46.182
about the roles that God
created for man and woman.

32:47.308 --> 32:49.394
I had such high hopes
for this one here.

32:51.479 --> 32:54.274
So Mikey, you want to stay

32:54.315 --> 32:56.442
and help the women
with the dishes?

33:00.738 --> 33:02.365
Michael.

33:02.406 --> 33:04.324
Oh, doing the dishes
won't kill you, Liz.

33:04.367 --> 33:05.742
You do them most
of the time anyway.

33:05.784 --> 33:06.743
You're letting
him come in here

33:06.786 --> 33:08.872
and tell your wife what to do?

33:08.913 --> 33:10.415
A husband should be able to do

33:10.455 --> 33:12.416
whatever he chooses in his home.

33:13.334 --> 33:15.128
His castle.

33:15.168 --> 33:16.588
Is that so?

33:16.628 --> 33:17.838
Well in this house...

33:17.880 --> 33:20.340
You will not cause
a scene in my home.

33:20.383 --> 33:23.595
You see how my mom just got up
without a word of complaint?

33:23.636 --> 33:25.512
You can learn a thing
or two from her.

33:37.858 --> 33:40.360
It's no reason to
be so upset dear.

33:40.403 --> 33:41.404
Bernie's, right.

33:42.530 --> 33:44.907
Washing dishes is not
a chore for a boy.

33:44.948 --> 33:46.533
So you're okay with
all this role stuff?

33:46.576 --> 33:49.495
There've always been
roles for men and women

33:49.537 --> 33:54.542
and if we are to be good wives
as the good Lord instructs,

33:55.460 --> 33:56.627
we acknowledge those roles.

33:56.668 --> 33:59.213
So just submit, under
every circumstance.

34:00.714 --> 34:02.591
Under every circumstance.

34:02.634 --> 34:04.426
Michael's a great
man, Elizabeth,

34:04.469 --> 34:05.761
and you should be grateful that

34:05.802 --> 34:08.347
you have someone who
treats you so well.

34:10.600 --> 34:12.352
He is a great man.

34:13.602 --> 34:16.563
He's just not a great husband.

34:17.731 --> 34:19.900
I can't believe
I'm hearing this.

34:19.943 --> 34:22.278
He treats you like a queen.

34:22.319 --> 34:24.530
Yes, sometimes.

34:24.571 --> 34:27.825
And then sometimes he's abusive.

34:30.620 --> 34:31.578
Is Michael hitting you?

34:31.620 --> 34:33.664
No, no, he's just...

34:33.705 --> 34:35.582
Well then how is it abuse?

34:35.624 --> 34:36.833
I don't know.

34:37.752 --> 34:40.004
I don't know if it's
abuse, I just, I feel...

34:40.046 --> 34:43.633
We are here to help our
husbands reach their greatness

34:44.551 --> 34:46.553
and that's not always easy.

34:47.636 --> 34:48.513
I'm just not happy.

34:51.432 --> 34:52.392
I don't know why.

34:52.432 --> 34:53.976
You'll figure it out
what's wrong with you.

34:55.937 --> 34:57.397
Wrong with me?

34:57.437 --> 34:59.606
Our husbands are
exceptional men.

34:59.649 --> 35:03.486
They don't curse, or hit us,
or step out with other women.

35:03.528 --> 35:06.321
Yeah.

35:06.363 --> 35:08.992
Can we keep this
conversation just between us?

35:10.118 --> 35:11.661
Like it never happened, dear.

35:12.787 --> 35:14.539
Please, will you
rinse these dishes?

35:14.580 --> 35:15.622
My knees need a break.

35:15.664 --> 35:16.999
Of course, I'm sorry.

35:17.040 --> 35:18.417
Please, rest.

35:20.544 --> 35:23.798
Michael's trying to fill
some pretty big shoes.

35:23.839 --> 35:25.758
Try and give him
a break, ya hear?

35:34.725 --> 35:37.729
♪ The angels for me ♪

35:39.022 --> 35:40.690
You don't have
to stop singing,

35:40.731 --> 35:41.648
Look what I found.

35:42.774 --> 35:45.485
Surprise, so you
don't have to feel

35:45.528 --> 35:47.696
so uncomfortable
about being so pitchy.

35:48.781 --> 35:51.618
I'm glad you and my mom got
to spend some time together.

35:51.658 --> 35:52.618
Mhm.

35:52.660 --> 35:53.536
That's all?

35:54.787 --> 35:56.414
Can we talk about this later?

35:56.455 --> 35:57.789
I have some things on my mind.

35:59.167 --> 36:01.794
Like what you were
talking to my mom about?

36:03.171 --> 36:04.714
Excuse me?

36:04.756 --> 36:05.798
Well, I saw you
talking quietly

36:05.839 --> 36:07.716
to her while she
was washing dishes.

36:07.758 --> 36:11.470
So what were you talking about?

36:13.180 --> 36:14.307
I asked you a question.

36:14.348 --> 36:16.684
That's really between your
mother and me and Michael.

36:18.852 --> 36:20.646
Your husband is
asking you a question.

36:20.687 --> 36:22.773
Can I just finish
these dishes?

36:22.814 --> 36:23.816
We can talk later.

36:25.609 --> 36:26.861
Your husband's
asking you a question,

36:26.903 --> 36:27.986
and that means we talk now.

36:28.028 --> 36:30.781
I asked, I'm asking for space.

36:33.075 --> 36:35.577
Wives submit to
your husbands as God.

36:35.620 --> 36:36.746
I know the scripture.

36:36.787 --> 36:38.872
What were you talking
to my mother about?

36:39.832 --> 36:42.502
You and me Michael, we
were talking about us.

36:44.754 --> 36:45.797
I already knew that.

36:48.800 --> 36:50.051
You don't think my mother

36:50.093 --> 36:52.678
would keep something like
that from me, do you?

36:52.720 --> 36:54.305
She couldn't wait
to run and tell you.

36:54.347 --> 36:55.765
This isn't about her,

36:55.807 --> 36:56.890
this is about you
and your defiance

36:56.932 --> 36:58.100
and you're going behind my back.

36:58.142 --> 36:58.935
Defiance?

36:58.977 --> 37:00.185
Yes.

37:00.227 --> 37:01.854
I don't want to talk
about this right now.

37:01.896 --> 37:03.939
Yeah, well you don't really
have that option, do you?

37:13.783 --> 37:15.285
Who else have you
been talking to?

37:16.160 --> 37:17.245
Your mother?

37:17.287 --> 37:19.205
Is this what we're doing now?

37:19.247 --> 37:21.249
Ignoring me when we're talking?

37:21.290 --> 37:22.709
You're talking Michael.

37:22.749 --> 37:23.626
I'm just here.

37:24.669 --> 37:26.838
You can follow me all over
the house if you want to

37:26.879 --> 37:28.923
but you can not force me
to have a conversation

37:28.964 --> 37:30.883
that I don't want to have.

37:30.925 --> 37:32.926
Son, when it comes time
for you to pick out a wife

37:32.968 --> 37:35.179
make sure you find one who
is respectful and obedient.

37:35.220 --> 37:36.847
How dare you
bring him into this?

37:36.890 --> 37:39.100
My responsibility as
a parent is to make sure

37:39.142 --> 37:41.810
that he is capable of making
the right decisions in life.

37:41.852 --> 37:42.896
That's right, son.

37:48.776 --> 37:50.904
Let's go to the store.

37:50.944 --> 37:51.863
Okay.

37:54.948 --> 37:57.242
And where do you
think you're going?

37:57.285 --> 37:59.328
Get back in the house.

37:59.370 --> 38:01.915
We just want to
go for ice cream.

38:01.955 --> 38:03.999
Yeah, so get out of our way.

38:04.042 --> 38:06.169
You're not going anywhere.

38:08.046 --> 38:08.963
You hear me?

38:09.004 --> 38:11.965
You're not going anywhere.

38:12.008 --> 38:14.468
Okay, I'm sorry, I'll stay.

38:14.510 --> 38:17.804
Faith, why does
your mom always

38:17.847 --> 38:20.390
wear sunglasses even inside?

38:22.185 --> 38:25.230
Her eyes are
sensitive to light.

38:25.271 --> 38:30.276
Oh, my mom told my dad that
she always has bruises too.

38:30.818 --> 38:33.278
She just falls a lot.

38:33.321 --> 38:36.281
She's really clumsy sometimes.

38:36.323 --> 38:37.492
Oh.

38:37.533 --> 38:40.827
Hey girls, do
y'all want a snack?

38:40.870 --> 38:42.038
Okay.

38:44.039 --> 38:45.999
You're the best mom ever.

38:50.088 --> 38:53.048
No, I'm not, but
I'm trying, baby.

38:57.386 --> 38:59.388
You don't have to do that.

38:59.430 --> 39:00.973
I'm coming to apologize.

39:01.015 --> 39:03.268
I never should've brought
Matthew into this.

39:06.144 --> 39:08.021
Is that all you're
apologizing for?

39:10.066 --> 39:11.401
What else is there?

39:16.113 --> 39:17.030
What are you doing?

39:18.867 --> 39:20.325
It's been four days Liz.

39:23.328 --> 39:24.162
And?

39:25.330 --> 39:28.334
And I'm struggling.

39:31.004 --> 39:35.175
This is why so many marriages
open up to temptation.

39:35.216 --> 39:38.219
There are certain things that
are expected of you as a wife.

39:41.263 --> 39:43.557
So I'm just
supposed to say yes

39:43.600 --> 39:45.393
every time you want to have sex,

39:45.435 --> 39:47.353
even if I don't want to,

39:47.394 --> 39:50.063
because that's my
duty as a wife?

39:50.106 --> 39:51.107
Yes.

39:52.107 --> 39:54.234
Just like how you expect
me to go out and make money

39:54.276 --> 39:56.612
because that's my
duty as a husband.

40:00.200 --> 40:02.535
I'm not having sex with
you tonight, Michael.

40:04.162 --> 40:07.247
So you can do, you can do
whatever you decide to do.

40:09.167 --> 40:09.959
Michael, let go of me.

40:10.001 --> 40:12.252
You are still my wife.

40:12.294 --> 40:14.379
We are of the same flesh Lizzy.

40:14.421 --> 40:15.464
Michael.

40:15.506 --> 40:17.966
Do not deny your husband.

40:18.008 --> 40:19.968
Michael, you're hurting me.

40:20.010 --> 40:21.011
Come, shh, shh, shh.

40:27.100 --> 40:29.604
Tell me you love me Lizzy.

40:29.646 --> 40:31.231
I love you so much.

40:33.316 --> 40:34.192
Tell me that.

40:36.568 --> 40:37.736
Michael.

40:39.280 --> 40:40.490
Lizzy, I love you so much.

40:41.490 --> 40:44.201
I love you so much, I love you.

40:51.459 --> 40:55.504
♪ I'm surrounded by shadows ♪

40:55.546 --> 40:57.631
♪ Rising up from
the floor boards ♪

40:57.673 --> 41:01.093
♪ Like black smoke ♪

41:01.135 --> 41:03.220
♪ They come alive
when the light's out ♪

41:03.263 --> 41:05.306
♪ And the silence is so loud ♪

41:05.347 --> 41:09.142
♪ I'm surrounded by shadows ♪

41:12.647 --> 41:13.815
Where's Faith?

41:13.856 --> 41:16.441
Sleeping
over at Zoey's tonight.

41:16.484 --> 41:21.406
Oh, so that means it's
just me and you tonight huh?

41:23.700 --> 41:24.533
I guess so.

41:26.285 --> 41:27.369
Something wrong with you?

41:29.664 --> 41:30.790
I have something for you.

41:38.464 --> 41:42.385
Faith's been hearing
you hitting me, she knows.

41:42.426 --> 41:45.220
Kids know that their parents
argue from time to time.

41:45.263 --> 41:46.139
It's no big deal.

41:47.390 --> 41:49.893
The big deal is
we aren't arguing.

41:49.934 --> 41:52.604
I don't want her to
think that it's okay.

41:52.644 --> 41:53.812
All of that's in the past.

41:53.854 --> 41:55.856
And the past seems to
keep repeating itself.

41:55.899 --> 41:56.732
I gave you my word.

41:56.774 --> 41:57.609
Again.

42:01.571 --> 42:04.365
I bought you flowers,
you love flowers.

42:04.406 --> 42:05.825
You're not gonna
thank me for that?

42:05.867 --> 42:06.910
No.

42:06.950 --> 42:07.952
Take the flowers.

42:07.993 --> 42:09.287
And then what?

42:09.328 --> 42:10.955
We start all over tomorrow.

42:10.997 --> 42:12.457
I said that that
was in the past.

42:12.497 --> 42:13.624
Why are you trying
to start a fight?

42:13.665 --> 42:15.584
You can't buy my
forgiveness anymore.

42:16.919 --> 42:18.421
Meaning?

42:18.463 --> 42:19.839
What would you say to
your daughter if you knew

42:19.881 --> 42:21.925
some man was giving
her black eyes?

42:21.966 --> 42:23.426
What would you tell
her to do Derek?

42:23.468 --> 42:24.636
You thinking about leaving me?

42:24.676 --> 42:26.220
Would you try to stop me?

42:28.097 --> 42:29.265
If I had to.

42:31.559 --> 42:32.352
Look, look, look, look,

42:32.392 --> 42:34.269
okay, okay, okay,
listen, listen, look.

42:34.312 --> 42:39.317
I have these beautiful
flowers here, for you.

42:39.984 --> 42:40.944
I've apologized for all that

42:40.984 --> 42:42.819
other stuff that
happened before.

42:42.861 --> 42:44.488
So let the past
just be the past.

42:45.656 --> 42:50.370
Now, are you going to
take these flowers?

42:51.412 --> 42:53.455
Or am I going to have to
give them to somebody else?

42:53.497 --> 42:55.582
Don't nobody want your
ugly ass sunflowers.

43:21.109 --> 43:21.943
Damn!

43:24.696 --> 43:25.613
You see?

43:25.655 --> 43:26.823
I try to do something nice for

43:26.865 --> 43:28.867
your ungrateful ass,
but you want to fight.

43:28.908 --> 43:31.743
Don't come out of this room
until your attitude is right.

43:49.428 --> 43:52.682
Where are you going?

43:52.723 --> 43:53.640
To the bathroom.

44:42.064 --> 44:43.106
Lizzy?

45:16.057 --> 45:18.309
Hey, how long are you
going to be in there?

46:51.318 --> 46:53.403
Tanya.

46:53.446 --> 46:54.822
Hey, Sarge.

46:54.863 --> 46:55.990
We got a call
about loud voices,

46:56.031 --> 46:57.242
yelling coming from your place.

46:57.283 --> 46:58.451
This is officer Banks.

46:58.493 --> 46:59.911
Just transferred
in from up north.

46:59.952 --> 47:01.036
Do you
mind if we come in

47:01.078 --> 47:02.372
and speak to both of you?

47:02.412 --> 47:03.956
Well all of that
really isn't necessary.

47:03.997 --> 47:05.290
Well I'd still
like to speak to you,

47:05.332 --> 47:06.166
if that's not a problem.

47:06.209 --> 47:07.085
Yeah Derek,

47:07.126 --> 47:08.502
we probably should
talk to both of you.

47:08.544 --> 47:09.796
Tanya!

47:09.836 --> 47:11.463
Excuse the mess.

47:11.506 --> 47:15.468
Wife isn't much of a home
maker, but she can cook.

47:18.136 --> 47:19.847
So I guess that makes up for it.

47:23.142 --> 47:25.060
I'll speak with
the wife separately.

47:34.153 --> 47:35.196
Hi, I'm officer Banks.

47:35.238 --> 47:37.573
Tanya, Derek's wife.

47:37.615 --> 47:39.450
You mind telling me
what happened tonight?

47:41.118 --> 47:43.245
Me and my husband just
had a little disagreement.

47:43.287 --> 47:45.080
From the looks of the
scratches on his face,

47:45.122 --> 47:46.624
I would say it's a little
more than a disagreement.

47:46.665 --> 47:49.126
You wanna tell me about those?

47:49.167 --> 47:53.213
I lost my balance and
reached out for his hand,

47:53.256 --> 47:54.339
and completely missed.

47:54.381 --> 47:55.258
I see.

47:57.385 --> 47:58.970
Were you defending yourself?

48:02.598 --> 48:04.309
Would you like to
speak in private?

48:05.642 --> 48:06.476
No.

48:08.687 --> 48:11.148
Do you realize every
time I ask you a question,

48:11.191 --> 48:12.274
you look at your husband?

48:15.569 --> 48:16.613
You're still doing it.

48:20.033 --> 48:21.910
Look at me, I'll ask you again.

48:21.950 --> 48:24.036
Would you like to
speak to me in private?

48:25.412 --> 48:28.081
No, I'm okay.

48:28.124 --> 48:29.292
We're okay.

48:29.334 --> 48:31.085
I can't help if you don't ask.

48:46.184 --> 48:47.060
Nothing here.

48:47.100 --> 48:48.102
He's one of us.

48:50.229 --> 48:52.147
You're really lucky.

48:52.189 --> 48:54.149
This officer has
clearly been assaulted.

48:54.191 --> 48:55.150
He's a good man.

48:56.276 --> 48:57.694
Make sure you're
taking care of him.

49:01.073 --> 49:03.242
Don't hesitate
to call if you need us.

49:03.283 --> 49:05.118
Thank you.

49:05.160 --> 49:08.121
You know, every time I
asked your wife a question,

49:08.164 --> 49:09.457
she would look to see
if you were watching

49:09.499 --> 49:11.167
and every time you were.

49:11.209 --> 49:15.088
If I was hitting my wife,
like you seem to be implying,

49:16.256 --> 49:18.007
why wouldn't she just
have me locked up?

49:18.048 --> 49:19.091
Man, she loves you.

49:20.260 --> 49:22.178
She just doesn't want
to see you in jail.

49:22.220 --> 49:23.763
She wants you to
stop beating on her.

49:23.805 --> 49:25.390
Like I said before, there's
nothing going on here.

49:25.430 --> 49:27.307
Banks, go
wait in the car.

49:39.153 --> 49:40.071
Listen man.

49:40.988 --> 49:42.155
This is the fourth time
we've been out here.

49:42.198 --> 49:45.660
There's never been
any charges filed, no arrests.

49:45.702 --> 49:46.828
It's one thing if
it was officer Cooper

49:46.870 --> 49:50.080
but this new guy can cause
some real problems for you.

49:51.207 --> 49:52.292
Just keep it down.

49:53.501 --> 49:55.252
It's not worth the
jail time brother.

49:55.294 --> 49:57.629
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
I'll take care of it.

49:57.671 --> 49:58.673
Appreciate it.

49:58.714 --> 49:59.506
Ya'll be good.

49:59.548 --> 50:00.507
All right.

50:15.439 --> 50:17.316
You won't be happy till you
see me in jail, will you?

50:17.357 --> 50:19.359
If I wanted you in jail,
I would have told him.

50:19.401 --> 50:20.403
Told him what?

50:21.613 --> 50:23.531
Better be glad I
didn't press charges.

50:25.408 --> 50:26.451
But don't worry baby.

50:27.202 --> 50:31.122
I won't let them lock
you up, this time.

50:34.292 --> 50:35.418
We could be a perfect team

50:36.586 --> 50:39.339
if you had just
taken the flowers.

50:43.468 --> 50:44.385
Good night.

50:45.511 --> 50:47.430
Good night Derek.

50:55.479 --> 50:56.731
Hey, Lizzy?

51:42.443 --> 51:43.486
I love you.

51:46.071 --> 51:48.740
You know I love you right, yeah?

51:54.080 --> 51:55.999
I don't wanna hurt you.

51:56.915 --> 51:57.749
I don't.

52:02.379 --> 52:04.965
You trying to leave me hm?

52:05.008 --> 52:07.551
You're trying to leave me?

52:07.593 --> 52:08.595
No?

52:10.763 --> 52:11.973
Okay.

52:12.015 --> 52:13.600
Good, till death
do us part, right?

52:14.600 --> 52:15.767
Right?

52:17.019 --> 52:17.853
Okay, okay.

52:20.731 --> 52:25.652
I love you.

52:25.694 --> 52:26.528
Okay.

52:28.156 --> 52:30.074
Good night, good night.

53:14.702 --> 53:15.662
Hi.

53:21.792 --> 53:24.169
How could you embarrass
the church like this?

53:25.296 --> 53:26.839
How could you
embarrass me like this?

53:26.881 --> 53:28.883
I'm sure people are
already talking.

53:31.635 --> 53:33.053
What were you
thinking about Liz?

53:37.892 --> 53:40.144
Good morning Pastor Jeffries,
I'm minister Ross Day.

53:40.185 --> 53:42.729
I was just coming by to
check on Ms. Jeffries.

53:42.772 --> 53:44.148
Hi, all right.

53:44.189 --> 53:45.732
How are you
feeling today ma'am?

53:45.774 --> 53:47.568
She's
not speaking much.

53:48.318 --> 53:50.612
Feeling much better.

53:50.655 --> 53:53.658
Would you mind if I spoke
to Ms. Jeffries alone?

53:53.700 --> 53:55.993
Oh, we don't keep any
secrets from one another.

53:56.035 --> 53:58.788
It's just
protocol at this hospital.

53:58.830 --> 54:00.248
I hope you understand.

54:00.289 --> 54:03.292
I'll be right outside,
just a wave if you need me.

54:05.879 --> 54:06.963
Ms. Jeffries.

54:09.173 --> 54:12.843
Please, please
call me Elizabeth.

54:12.885 --> 54:14.803
As part of what I do
here at the hospital

54:14.845 --> 54:17.097
I have to ask you some
difficult questions.

54:18.098 --> 54:19.767
I understand.

54:19.809 --> 54:21.810
What happened last night
to bring you to this point?

54:38.995 --> 54:40.330
He can't hear you.

54:41.247 --> 54:42.080
Thank you.

54:43.790 --> 54:46.836
Last night, my husband and I,

54:46.877 --> 54:48.879
we got into a heated argument.

54:49.756 --> 54:54.969
He came in later and
he wanted to have sex.

54:56.470 --> 54:57.888
I was still upset with him,

54:57.930 --> 55:01.892
so I denied him and
he, he did it anyway.

55:01.935 --> 55:03.436
Are you saying he forced you?

55:04.812 --> 55:07.732
You make it so,
sounds so violent

55:07.774 --> 55:09.234
when you say it like that.

55:09.274 --> 55:11.276
He's my husband.

55:11.318 --> 55:12.903
It wasn't rape.

55:12.946 --> 55:14.322
We're married and um.

55:15.948 --> 55:18.867
You shouldn't be guilted
or forced into having sex.

55:18.910 --> 55:22.413
If it's not
consensual, it is rape.

55:22.455 --> 55:23.665
A husband can't rape his wife.

55:23.705 --> 55:26.291
Yes Elizabeth,
marital rape exists.

55:26.334 --> 55:28.377
Michael has never
been violent with me.

55:31.464 --> 55:34.175
I mean I wasn't in danger, I
didn't even scream for help.

55:34.216 --> 55:35.968
Well, I think this
is a scream for help.

55:36.970 --> 55:37.846
And you are in danger.

55:37.886 --> 55:39.388
If you think that the
only way to escape

55:39.430 --> 55:41.140
is to take your life.

55:41.182 --> 55:42.475
I'm not telling you what
to do in your marriage

55:42.517 --> 55:45.812
but what I will say is
that your life matters.

55:45.854 --> 55:47.897
It is important that you
take care of yourself,

55:47.939 --> 55:50.817
of your body, as
well as your soul.

55:50.859 --> 55:52.777
I can't just walk
out on a marriage.

55:55.405 --> 55:56.196
Right?

55:56.238 --> 55:57.531
I don't like divorce.

55:57.573 --> 55:59.992
But I think that
sometimes it's necessary.

56:00.033 --> 56:01.118
Why don't we just talk

56:01.160 --> 56:02.995
about that when
you're feeling better?

56:04.037 --> 56:04.997
Yeah.

56:05.039 --> 56:07.917
Lizzy, the nurses say
it's time for breakfast.

56:12.171 --> 56:15.091
I'll be around if you need
me for prayer or anything.

56:17.135 --> 56:18.845
It's a pleasure
to meet you both.

56:24.600 --> 56:27.102
Well.

56:27.144 --> 56:29.188
What were the two of
you talking about?

56:29.229 --> 56:30.356
I'm tired Michael.

56:33.318 --> 56:36.153
I can eat a little breakfast,
but then I need to rest.

56:44.495 --> 56:45.455
Got a minute.

56:45.495 --> 56:47.122
Yeah, come on in.

56:47.164 --> 56:48.957
I missed you last Sunday.

56:48.999 --> 56:52.419
I was
sick, much better though.

56:52.461 --> 56:54.254
I've been wanting
to talk to you.

56:55.589 --> 56:57.216
Yeah, have a seat.

57:03.640 --> 57:07.352
So you wanted to talk to me?

57:07.392 --> 57:09.144
Well I did.

57:09.187 --> 57:11.147
Now that I'm here I
don't know what to say.

57:11.189 --> 57:13.232
Did you want to talk
to me about Faith?

57:15.276 --> 57:18.655
or Derek?

57:18.696 --> 57:20.490
Derek or me.

57:24.535 --> 57:26.537
He attacked me again.

57:27.580 --> 57:29.749
Hey, I am so sorry.

57:30.792 --> 57:32.168
Did you call the police?

57:32.209 --> 57:34.294
He is the police.

57:34.336 --> 57:35.338
Okay.

57:39.466 --> 57:41.385
There are shelters
that you can go to.

57:42.345 --> 57:46.015
They have counselors and
legal representation.

57:46.057 --> 57:47.433
You'd be protected there.

57:47.475 --> 57:50.270
I have Faith to look after,
I can't just move her to.

57:51.229 --> 57:54.189
Look, he's good to her.

57:54.231 --> 57:57.609
How good is he to her if
he's trying to kill her mother?

58:01.238 --> 58:03.282
Shelter is just not an option.

58:04.283 --> 58:06.035
Okay.

58:06.077 --> 58:07.287
So what are you going to do?

58:09.372 --> 58:11.832
Keep my head
down, my mouth shut.

58:11.874 --> 58:14.293
It's not your fault.

58:14.334 --> 58:15.336
You know that right?

58:16.754 --> 58:20.175
Abuse is about
power and control.

58:20.216 --> 58:21.551
Well, he has both.

58:21.593 --> 58:22.760
What do you need from me?

58:22.801 --> 58:24.720
Tell me what to do.

58:24.761 --> 58:28.182
Leave him, by any
means necessary.

58:28.223 --> 58:30.559
There's a safe place I can
give you information on.

58:39.234 --> 58:41.320
They can help you
with resources.

58:41.361 --> 58:43.280
They can help get
you on your feet.

58:43.323 --> 58:44.656
I don't know.

58:44.698 --> 58:46.325
Try them.

58:46.367 --> 58:48.160
Make sure you have all
your important documents,

58:48.202 --> 58:50.287
birth certificates, passports.

58:50.330 --> 58:53.290
Maybe even get a prepaid
phone so you can't be tracked.

58:53.332 --> 58:55.376
They can help you
with an escape plan.

58:55.417 --> 58:56.877
What if he kills me?

58:56.919 --> 58:57.878
I won't lie.

58:59.004 --> 59:01.840
The most dangerous time will
be when you try to leave.

59:01.883 --> 59:04.385
Take his threats seriously.

59:04.426 --> 59:05.636
If you have a plan,

59:06.763 --> 59:09.182
you can be one of the
ones that make it.

59:09.223 --> 59:10.892
I just don't know
if I can risk it.

59:12.852 --> 59:14.896
I have Faith to take care of.

59:17.439 --> 59:19.358
What would she do
without her mother?

59:19.399 --> 59:20.359
Exactly.

59:24.446 --> 59:26.698
Well, I better get going.

59:27.533 --> 59:30.452
I don't want him
wondering where I'm at.

59:43.383 --> 59:45.426
Faith honey, why don't
you to go upstairs

59:45.468 --> 59:46.886
and get out of your
church clothes?

59:46.928 --> 59:48.888
Not before you give
your daddy a hug.

59:55.687 --> 59:57.397
Where have y'all
been today sweet pea?

59:57.437 --> 59:58.606
Just to church.

59:59.982 --> 1:00:02.568
Did you go anywhere
after church?

1:00:02.609 --> 1:00:04.778
No, just home.

1:00:06.531 --> 1:00:10.827
Was mommy talking to the
deacons or her church friends?

1:00:10.868 --> 1:00:12.035
I don't know.

1:00:12.077 --> 1:00:14.496
I stay into my class
until she gets me.

1:00:14.539 --> 1:00:16.707
I was like the last
one in there today.

1:00:16.749 --> 1:00:19.794
But Ms. Sanders gave
me extra piece of candy

1:00:19.836 --> 1:00:21.421
so it was fine with me.

1:00:21.461 --> 1:00:22.463
I bet it was.

1:00:23.631 --> 1:00:24.424
Well why don't you head up

1:00:24.464 --> 1:00:27.635
to your castle
princess and change up?

1:00:27.676 --> 1:00:32.390
On the count of three, one,
two, three, go, go, go, go.

1:00:40.022 --> 1:00:41.649
What took you so long
to get her from class?

1:00:41.691 --> 1:00:42.901
First lady's been out sick.

1:00:42.941 --> 1:00:44.776
I just stopped by to
speak to her for a minute.

1:00:44.818 --> 1:00:45.986
About me?

1:00:46.028 --> 1:00:48.614
Of course not,
about church stuff.

1:00:49.823 --> 1:00:50.657
Good.

1:00:52.785 --> 1:00:56.664
You know, I have never
been shot before,

1:00:57.457 --> 1:01:01.920
but I have heard how
painful it is when it...

1:01:04.214 --> 1:01:05.089
Rips through you.

1:01:12.472 --> 1:01:13.723
Don't be so serious.

1:01:15.015 --> 1:01:16.184
I'm just cleaning them.

1:01:16.225 --> 1:01:19.436
Never know when you'll
need to use one.

1:01:35.160 --> 1:01:36.828
Happy anniversary, darling.

1:01:54.180 --> 1:01:58.810
Look, I know our relationship
has been rocky lately

1:01:58.852 --> 1:02:01.062
but I want our
marriage to be strong.

1:02:01.104 --> 1:02:02.522
Like it always has been.

1:02:17.327 --> 1:02:18.704
A book.

1:02:18.745 --> 1:02:20.247
Well, not just any
book, here, look at it.

1:02:21.790 --> 1:02:25.794
How To Properly Care For
And Serve Your Husband.

1:02:25.836 --> 1:02:26.920
I know it gets confusing

1:02:26.963 --> 1:02:29.089
for women to know
what their role is.

1:02:29.131 --> 1:02:30.300
And this book right here

1:02:30.341 --> 1:02:32.676
redefines what it means
to be a good wife.

1:02:32.718 --> 1:02:34.761
Here, I even highlighted
some of the passages

1:02:34.803 --> 1:02:38.932
that I thought you
might find enlightening.

1:02:43.312 --> 1:02:47.274
How to turn your not right
now's into right away dear.

1:02:52.030 --> 1:02:52.863
Oh my God.

1:03:02.457 --> 1:03:04.000
That was uncalled for.

1:03:04.042 --> 1:03:07.837
No, that book
was uncalled for.

1:04:08.314 --> 1:04:10.316
We've all been
praying for you, Liz

1:04:12.109 --> 1:04:15.363
and since we heard
about your accident.

1:04:19.908 --> 1:04:24.872
Because the severity of the
situation of what happened

1:04:27.165 --> 1:04:30.294
we think that, that you should.

1:04:32.046 --> 1:04:34.464
You should step
down from counseling

1:04:34.506 --> 1:04:37.050
until everything gets
back to normal with you.

1:04:44.975 --> 1:04:46.019
And this was your idea?

1:04:46.060 --> 1:04:49.105
You know, you've had issues
with her anxiety before

1:04:49.147 --> 1:04:50.190
and now it's the pills.

1:04:50.231 --> 1:04:52.984
My medical history is private.

1:04:53.026 --> 1:04:54.068
This is not the time.

1:04:54.109 --> 1:04:56.111
I have always
been there for you.

1:04:56.153 --> 1:04:59.364
If you can't make the
hard decisions, I can.

1:05:01.993 --> 1:05:03.119
I think
pastors just trying

1:05:03.160 --> 1:05:04.912
